    <question>
        <prompt>What was the purpose of the "Iron Clad Oath"?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To prevent former Confederates from holding office</option>
            <option letter="b">To support Confederate veterans</option>
            <option letter="c">To regulate voting rights</option>
            <option letter="d">To control labor contracts</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Iron Clad Oath required individuals to swear they had never supported the Confederacy before holding public office, limiting former Confederates' political power.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What role did the "Pine Knot" strategy play in Reconstruction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Intimidated African American voters through night raids</option>
            <option letter="b">Protected freed slaves</option>
            <option letter="c">Supported education reform</option>
            <option letter="d">Promoted economic development</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Pine Knot strategy involved night raids by white supremacists using burning pine knots to intimidate African American voters and Republican supporters.</explanation>
